goals.question: What is the average wheat production and wages per year?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['wheat'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of wheat production over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Wheat Production')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['wheat'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['wheat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['wheat'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wheat production?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['wheat'], data['wages'])
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wheat production and wages?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Wheat Production')
    plt.ylabel('Wages')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['wages'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['wages'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['wages'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['wages'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['wages'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wages?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('year').mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(data.index, data['wheat'], color='blue', label='Wheat')
    ax.bar(data.index, data['wages'], color='orange', label='Wages')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average wheat production and wages per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
